<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <script>
      const chatHistory = document.getElementById("chatHistory");
      const openChatHistory = document.getElementById("openChatHistory");

      openChatHistory.addEventListener("click", () => {
        chatHistory.classList.toggle("show");
      });

      const humanMessages = ["Hello, I'm a chatbot. How can I help you?", "I'm not able to provide information on that topic."];
      const botMessages = ["Sure, here is the information you requested.", "Please provide me with more details about the topic you're interested in."];

      const displayMessages = () => {
        chatHistory.innerHTML = "";

        for (const message of humanMessages) {
          const humanMessageElement = document.createElement("div");
          humanMessageElement.classList.add("human-message");
          humanMessageElement.innerText = message;
          chatHistory.appendChild(humanMessageElement);
        }

        for (const message of botMessages) {
          const botMessageElement = document.createElement("div");
          botMessageElement.classList.add("bot-message");
          botMessageElement.innerText = message;
          chatHistory.appendChild(botMessageElement);
        }
      };

      displayMessages();
    </script>
  </head>

  <body>
    <button id="openChatHistory">Open Chat History</button>

    <div id="chatHistory" class="hidden">
      <h3>Chat History</h3>

      <div id="messages">
        <!-- Messages will be displayed here -->
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>
      displayMessages();
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
```

This code creates a modal that shows the previous messages exchanged between the human and the chatbot. It includes 2 messages from the human and 2 messages from the chatbot. The messages are displayed in separate div elements with different classes to distinguish between the human and bot messages.

